Train 20 minutes, 3 times per week

   Make your breaks and downtime more productive by taking just a few
   minutes to focus on the types of brainwaves that protect sleep.

   Examples Include:

Focus

   Each morning, focus on a single point and push away unnecessary
   thoughts.

Clear Your Mind

   Take a mid-day break to let your mind wander freely.

Mindful Minute

   Focus on breathing before going to sleep

